<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=741&amp;p=6403#p6403</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=741&amp;p=6403#p6403"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Simple Zelda MMC1 question]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=741&amp;p=6403#p6403"><![CDATA[
On MMC1 (and even MMC3) cartridges with CHR RAM, the bank select line(s) are usually still connected to the mapper chip, allowing the RAM to be banked like normal. However, most games will just map in the default banks and leave them as-is (though some do not, such as the Famicom RPG 'Lagrange Point').<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7">Quietust</a> — Wed Nov 09, 2005 6:09 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
